{"id":719,"parent_id":702,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":719,"title":"Isaiah 17","subtitle":"","short_title":"Isa.","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 17"],[".studySummary",["i","Israel was scattered because she forgot God—Yet the nations that plunder her will be destroyed."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.1","order":"02.24.017.46597"},["b","1"],"The",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"burden"],"of",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_1b"},"Damascus"],". Behold, Damascus is taken away from",["i","being"],"a city, and it shall be a ruinous heap."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.2","order":"02.24.017.46598"},["b","2"],"The cities of Aroer",["i","are"],"forsaken: they shall be for flocks, which shall lie down, and none shall make",["i","them"],"afraid."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.3","order":"02.24.017.46599"},["b","3"],"The fortress also shall cease from",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_3a"},"Ephraim"],", and the kingdom from Damascus, and the remnant of Syria: they shall be as the glory of the children of Israel, saith the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"of hosts."],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.4","order":"02.24.017.46600"},["b","4"],"And in that day it shall come to pass,",["i","that"],"the glory of Jacob shall be made thin, and the fatness of his flesh shall wax lean."],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.5","order":"02.24.017.46601"},["b","5"],"And it shall be as when the harvestman gathereth the corn, and reapeth the ears with his arm; and it shall be as he that gathereth ears in the valley of Rephaim."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.6","order":"02.24.017.46602"},["b","6"],"¶Yet",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"gleaning grapes"],"shall be left in it, as the shaking of an olive tree, two",["i","or"],"three berries in the top of the uppermost bough, four",["i","or"],"five in the outmost fruitful branches thereof, saith the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"God of Israel."],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.7","order":"02.24.017.46603"},["b","7"],"At that day shall a man look to his",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"Maker"],", and",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_7b"},"his"],"eyes shall have respect to the Holy One of Israel."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.8","order":"02.24.017.46604"},["b","8"],"And he shall not look to the altars, the work of his hands, neither shall respect",["i","that"],"which his fingers have made, either the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_8a"},"groves"],", or the images."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.9","order":"02.24.017.46605"},["b","9"],"¶In that day shall his strong cities be as a forsaken bough, and an uppermost branch, which they left because of the children of Israel: and there shall be desolation."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.10","order":"02.24.017.46606"},["b","10"],"Because",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_10a"},"thou"],"hast",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_10b"},"forgotten"],"the God of thy",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_10c"},"salvation"],", and hast not been mindful of the",["sup","d"],["a",{"href":"fn_10d"},"rock"],"of thy strength, therefore",["sup","e"],["a",{"href":"fn_10e"},"shalt thou plant"],"pleasant plants, and shalt set it with strange slips:"],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.11","order":"02.24.017.46607"},["b","11"],"In the day shalt thou make thy plant to grow, and in the morning shalt thou make thy seed to flourish:",["i","but"],"the harvest",["i","shall be"],"a heap in the day of grief and of desperate sorrow."],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.12","order":"02.24.017.46608"},["b","12"],"¶Woe to",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_12a"},"the"],"multitude of many people,",["i","which"],"make a noise like the noise of the seas; and to the rushing of nations,",["i","that"],"make a rushing like the rushing of mighty waters!"],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.13","order":"02.24.017.46609"},["b","13"],"The nations shall rush like the rushing of many waters: but",["i","God"],"shall rebuke them, and they shall flee far off, and shall be chased as the chaff of the mountains before the wind, and like a",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_13a"},"rolling"],"thing before the whirlwind."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.14","order":"02.24.017.46610"},["b","14"],"And behold at eveningtide trouble;",["i","and"],"before the morning he",["i","is"],"not. This",["i","is"],"the portion of them that",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_14a"},"spoil"],"us, and the lot of them that rob us."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.1a","order":"02.24.017.46611"},["b","1a"],["span.small","IE"],"a message of doom “lifted up” against Damascus."],["div",{"id":"1b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.1b","order":"02.24.017.46613"},["b","1b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/7.8"},"Isa. 7:8"],"."],["div",{"id":"3a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.3a","order":"02.24.017.46615"},["b","3a"],["span.small","IE"],"Syria and northern Israel (Ephraim) were allies, and both were soon to be conquered by Assyria.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/israel-joseph-people-of"},"TG Israel, Joseph, People of"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/israel-ten-lost-tribes-of"},"Israel, Ten Lost Tribes of"],"."],["div",{"id":"6a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.6a","order":"02.24.017.46617"},["b","6a"],["span.small","IE"],"only a small remnant of Israel will be found after Assyria’s conquest.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/israel-remnant-of"},"TG Israel, Remnant of"],"."],["div",{"id":"7a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.7a","order":"02.24.017.46619"},["b","7a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/hosea/8.14"},"Hosea 8:14"],"."],["div",{"id":"7b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.7b","order":"02.24.017.46621"},["b","7b"],["span.small","IE"],"In their bereavement they will begin to repent."],["div",{"id":"8a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.8a","order":"02.24.017.46623"},["b","8a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/micah/5.14"},"Micah 5:14"],"."],["div",{"id":"10a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.10a","order":"02.24.017.46625"},["b","10a"],["span.small","IE"],"Israel."],["div",{"id":"10b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.10b","order":"02.24.017.46627"},["b","10b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/7.20.17-22"},"Hel. 7:20 (17–22)"],"."],["div",{"id":"10c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.10c","order":"02.24.017.46629"},["b","10c"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/68.20.19-20"},"Ps. 68:20 (19–20)"],"."],["div",{"id":"10d","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.10d","order":"02.24.017.46631"},["b","10d"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/rock"},"TG Rock"],"."],["div",{"id":"10e","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.10e","order":"02.24.017.46633"},["b","10e"],["span.small","HEB"],"thou dost plant … ; i.e., practice idolatrous things."],["div",{"id":"12a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.12a","order":"02.24.017.46635"},["b","12a"],["span.small","IE"],"the Assyrian empire of numerous nations (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.12-14"},"vv. 12–14"],")."],["div",{"id":"13a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.13a","order":"02.24.017.46637"},["b","13a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/83.13"},"Ps. 83:13"],"."],["div",{"id":"14a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/isa/17.14a","order":"02.24.017.46639"},["b","14a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/33.1.1,4"},"Isa. 33:1 (1, 4)"],"."]]}
